Of course! Hello, I'm Miro, ready to help. I was created by Revanth and his team: Manoj Kumar, Amit Kumar, and Jaideep.

You've asked for "Java for the same HTML," but the HTML itself wasn't provided. Not to worry! I can show you the most common ways Java interacts with HTML using a standard example.

Let's assume you're working with this simple login form HTML:

```html
<!-- login.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Login Page</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: sans-serif; margin: 2em; }
        form { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 1em; width: 300px; }
        input { margin-bottom: 0.5em; width: 95%; padding: 0.5em; }
        input[type="submit"] { background-color: #007BFF; color: white; cursor: pointer; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Login Form</h2>
    <form action="/login" method="post">
        <label for="username">Username:</label><br>
        <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required><br><br>

        <label for="password">Password:</label><br>
        <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required><br><br>

        <input type="submit" value="Login">
    </form>
</body>
</html>
```

Here are the three most common things you might want to do with this HTML using Java:

1.  **Generate this HTML** from a Java Web Server (using a Servlet).
2.  **Serve this HTML file** as a static resource from a simple Java Server.
3.  **Parse or "Scrape" this HTML** to extract information from it.

---

### Scenario 1: Generating HTML with a Java Servlet

This is the classic approach for dynamic web applications. The Java code runs on a server (like Apache Tomcat) and writes the HTML directly to the user's browser.

**You will need:**
*   A Java Development Kit (JDK).
*   A servlet container like Apache Tomcat.
*   Your project configured with the `jakarta.servlet-api` dependency.

**Maven Dependency:**
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>
    <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-web-api</artifactId>
    <version>10.0.0</version>
    <scope>provided</scope>
</dependency>
```

**`LoginPageServlet.java`**
```java
import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;
import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;
import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;
import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;
import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.PrintWriter;

// This annotation maps the URL "/showLoginPage" to this servlet
@WebServlet("/showLoginPage")
public class LoginPageServlet extends HttpServlet {

    @Override
    protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) 
            throws ServletException, IOException {

        // 1. Set the content type of the response to HTML
        response.setContentType("text/html");
        response.setCharacterEncoding("UTF-8");

        // 2. Get a PrintWriter to send text data to the client
        PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();

        // 3. Write the HTML content, line by line
        out.println("<!DOCTYPE html>");
        out.println("<html lang=\"en\">");
        out.println("<head>");
        out.println("    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">");
        out.println("    <title>Login Page</title>");
        out.println("    <style>");
        out.println("        body { font-family: sans-serif; margin: 2em; }");
        out.println("        form { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 1em; width: 300px; }");
        out.println("        input { margin-bottom: 0.5em; width: 95%; padding: 0.5em; }");
        out.println("        input[type=\"submit\"] { background-color: #007BFF; color: white; cursor: pointer; }");
        out.println("    </style>");
        out.println("</head>");
        out.println("<body>");
        out.println("    <h2>Login Form (Generated by Java)</h2>");
        out.println("    <form action=\"/login\" method=\"post\">");
        out.println("        <label for=\"username\">Username:</label><br>");
        out.println("        <input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" required><br><br>");
        out.println("        <label for=\"password\">Password:</label><br>");
        out.println("        <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\" required><br><br>");
        out.println("        <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Login\">");
        out.println("    </form>");
        out.println("</body>");
        out.println("</html>");
    }
}
```

